WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:04.120
Thank you, Huck.

00:04.120 --> 00:07.170
♪♪

00:12.170 --> 00:14.290
Oh, my God.

00:14.290 --> 00:18.540
[ Silenced gunshots ]

00:18.540 --> 00:21.330
♪♪

00:22.830 --> 00:25.500
[ Door beeping ]

00:27.330 --> 00:29.880
[ Door beeping ]

00:31.120 --> 00:33.460
[ Door beeps once ]

00:33.460 --> 00:35.960
♪♪

00:39.380 --> 00:41.380
Jennifer?

00:41.380 --> 00:42.620
[ Trunk opens ]

00:42.620 --> 00:45.420
♪♪

00:57.620 --> 00:59.080
[ Trunk closes ]

01:03.500 --> 01:04.500
What do you know
about them?

01:04.500 --> 01:05.960
Nothing.
I don't know names.

01:05.960 --> 01:08.170
I don't know what they do, where
they work, where they live.

01:08.170 --> 01:09.420
I don't know anything
about them.

01:09.420 --> 01:11.000
Except for the fact
that they used your dad

01:11.000 --> 01:12.210
to kill the president-elect
of the United States.

01:12.210 --> 01:13.460
And I want to know why.

01:13.460 --> 01:15.290
Where is she?
Who?

01:15.290 --> 01:17.120
Did you bring her here?
What -- What did you do?

01:17.120 --> 01:19.120
What are you talking about?
Who are you looking for?

01:19.120 --> 01:20.790
Jennifer Fields.
She's gone.

01:20.790 --> 01:22.170
What?
And the people in this room
are the only people

01:22.170 --> 01:24.170
who knew
where she was.

01:24.170 --> 01:25.750
Huck knew where she was.
He went to see her this morning.

01:25.750 --> 01:27.120
Why did Huck
go and see Jennifer?

01:27.120 --> 01:28.750
He took Meg to see her.

01:28.750 --> 01:29.620
Are you all thinking
what I'm thinking?

01:29.620 --> 01:30.920
Straight to voicemail.

01:30.920 --> 01:32.170
Huck almost never
turns his phone off,

01:32.170 --> 01:33.170
and he doesn't
let it die.

01:33.170 --> 01:34.580
Charlie?
I'm already there.

01:34.580 --> 01:35.920
Meg could be the mole.

01:35.920 --> 01:38.000
That bitch better not have
touched a hair on Huck's head.

01:38.000 --> 01:39.500
What's this?
The people you've
been looking for --

01:39.500 --> 01:40.830
find out who they are
and bring Huck back to me.

01:40.830 --> 01:42.750
[ Sighs ]
I want him back.

01:42.750 --> 01:44.040
[ Footsteps, door opens ]

01:44.040 --> 01:45.790
♪♪

01:45.790 --> 01:47.120
No sign of a struggle.

01:47.120 --> 01:49.120
Something happened.
I can feel it.

01:49.120 --> 01:52.170
♪♪

01:53.080 --> 01:54.880
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

02:04.380 --> 02:05.500
[ Sighs ]

02:05.500 --> 02:08.290
♪♪

02:17.750 --> 02:19.620
[ Sighs ]
Nothing.

02:19.620 --> 02:20.620
Look,
he'll be fine, Robin.

02:20.620 --> 02:22.170
He probably went
to go get some food.

02:22.170 --> 02:23.420
[ Sighs ]

02:23.420 --> 02:26.460
♪♪

02:27.710 --> 02:29.040
[ Gasps softly ]

02:32.540 --> 02:33.620
Start spraying.
Now you're wasting
your time.

02:33.620 --> 02:35.710
Start spraying.

02:35.710 --> 02:38.750
♪♪

02:52.960 --> 02:54.210
Hit the lights.

02:57.330 --> 02:58.460
Oh, my God.

02:58.460 --> 02:59.420
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

02:59.420 --> 03:01.920
[ Gasps ]

03:01.920 --> 03:03.790
Look at all
that blood.

03:03.790 --> 03:05.000
Oh, my God,
what did she do to him?

03:05.000 --> 03:06.420
Robin, I'm sorry.
No.

03:06.420 --> 03:08.000
No,
this isn't happening.

03:08.000 --> 03:09.040
Huck is fine.
I don't think so.

03:09.040 --> 03:10.250
Stop.
He's not dead.

03:10.250 --> 03:12.460
I'm just saying --
He's not dead, okay?!

03:16.920 --> 03:18.290
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

03:25.210 --> 03:28.710
Liv?
What are you doing?

03:28.710 --> 03:30.670
Huck,
he's -- he's gone.

03:30.670 --> 03:32.290
"Gone"?
He's missing.

03:32.290 --> 03:34.830
He's dating this girl,
Meg.

03:34.830 --> 03:36.580
This morning,
he took her to see someone,

03:36.580 --> 03:38.920
and now he's missing.

03:42.420 --> 03:46.710
Listen, you know Huck --
he goes dark sometimes.

03:46.710 --> 03:48.830
Falls off the wagon
and then back on and then off.

03:48.830 --> 03:51.250
No, Abby, this isn't --
this -- t-this isn't that.

03:51.250 --> 03:52.750
There are people.

03:52.750 --> 03:55.790
♪♪

03:59.790 --> 04:02.000
[ Whispering indistinctly ]

04:02.000 --> 04:03.380
Don't recognize them.
No, of course not.

04:03.380 --> 04:06.210
That's not...

04:06.210 --> 04:07.420
I'm here
because I need help.

04:07.420 --> 04:09.250
I need high-level
security clearance help.

04:09.250 --> 04:10.380
To find Huck.
Yes.

04:10.380 --> 04:11.620
I don't have
the best relationship

04:11.620 --> 04:12.670
with Fitz's girlfriend.

04:12.670 --> 04:14.290
FBI Director Webster.

04:14.290 --> 04:17.000
So, I was hoping that
you could get her this photo

04:17.000 --> 04:18.710
to run through
their imaging software,

04:18.710 --> 04:20.170
crosscheck their database.

04:20.170 --> 04:21.960
Maybe the FBI
can get a hit we can't.

04:21.960 --> 04:23.880
The FBI is a little busy
right now,

04:23.880 --> 04:25.710
dealing with the assassination
of the president-elect.

04:25.710 --> 04:27.250
Huck is missing.

04:27.250 --> 04:30.290
Huck could be dying
right now -- our Huck.

04:30.290 --> 04:31.330
You're right.
I'm sorry.

04:31.330 --> 04:33.210
Yes,
I will get it to Webster.

04:33.210 --> 04:34.750
Thanks, Abby.

04:36.330 --> 04:38.210
[ Clears throat ]

04:38.210 --> 04:41.000
♪♪

04:54.790 --> 04:56.670
[ Breathing raggedly ]

04:56.670 --> 04:58.460
[ Coughs ]

04:58.460 --> 05:00.290
[ Wheezing ]

05:00.290 --> 05:03.330
♪♪

05:10.540 --> 05:12.380
[ Grunts ]

05:12.380 --> 05:15.420
♪♪

05:20.000 --> 05:21.960
[ Car brakes squeaking ]

05:23.880 --> 05:25.620
[ Engine shuts off ]

05:25.620 --> 05:28.670
♪♪

05:31.620 --> 05:33.290
[ Breathing quickly ]

05:33.290 --> 05:36.330
♪♪

05:46.460 --> 05:49.210
[ Grunting ]

05:49.210 --> 05:52.250
♪♪

06:05.580 --> 06:07.670
[ Panting ]

06:07.670 --> 06:10.710
♪♪

06:25.170 --> 06:26.790
[ Yells ]
[ Water splashing ]

06:26.790 --> 06:29.830
♪♪

06:35.580 --> 06:37.750
[ Panting ]

06:41.120 --> 06:43.210
[ Gasping ]

06:43.210 --> 06:46.210
♪♪

06:57.170 --> 06:59.380
[ Thumping ]

07:00.670 --> 07:02.040
[ Thumping continues ]
[ Grunting ]

07:04.960 --> 07:06.710
Ow!

07:10.880 --> 07:12.790
[ Groaning ]

07:15.380 --> 07:17.000
[ Grunting ]
[ Thumping ]

07:21.750 --> 07:23.830
[ Screams ]

07:26.210 --> 07:27.670
[ Panting ]

07:33.540 --> 07:35.540
[ Steady, rhythmic thumping ]

07:38.750 --> 07:40.420
[ Breathing deeply ]

07:40.420 --> 07:42.380
[ Thumping continues ]

07:42.380 --> 07:45.420
♪♪

07:53.040 --> 07:55.120
[ Snaps fingers ]
Hey. Pay attention.

07:55.120 --> 07:56.380
[ Water sloshing ]

07:56.380 --> 07:58.580
[ Thumping continues ]

07:58.580 --> 08:01.710
♪♪

08:06.670 --> 08:07.790
How much time is left
on the clock?

08:07.790 --> 08:08.710
About 2 1/2 minutes.

08:08.710 --> 08:10.330
Then you need
to move, Huck.

08:10.330 --> 08:12.120
He's still in the trunk?

08:12.120 --> 08:13.170
I'd like to see
where you'd be.

08:13.170 --> 08:14.210
Not in the trunk,
that's for sure.

08:14.210 --> 08:15.210
[ Scoffs ] Please.

08:15.210 --> 08:17.420
Huck,
what was she driving?

08:19.210 --> 08:23.080
Huck, don't you dare
give up on me.

08:23.080 --> 08:25.540
You hear me?

08:25.540 --> 08:26.670
[ Echoing ] Do you?!

08:26.670 --> 08:28.120
[ Gasps ]

08:28.120 --> 08:29.880
[ Sputters ]
Whoa.

08:29.880 --> 08:32.120
Yes. I hear you.

08:32.120 --> 08:33.420
What was she driving?

08:33.420 --> 08:35.040
A Camry -- Corolla, maybe.

08:35.040 --> 08:36.920
Okay, we'll go with Camry.
Old model -- say, 2000?

08:36.920 --> 08:37.880
Sure.

08:37.880 --> 08:38.960
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

08:38.960 --> 08:40.750
Standard features
on a 2000 Camry --

08:40.750 --> 08:42.710
two DC power outlets,
12 volts each --

08:42.710 --> 08:44.250
convenient --
manual AC -- bummer --

08:44.250 --> 08:46.290
but, yes,
automatic windows.

08:46.290 --> 08:48.460
We're talking best case, here --
everybody gets that, right?

08:48.460 --> 08:50.540
Huck, can you get to the windows
from the trunk?

08:50.540 --> 08:53.580
♪♪

08:54.080 --> 08:55.710
[ Thumping ]

08:55.710 --> 08:57.330
[ Grunting ]

08:59.120 --> 09:01.000
[ Gasping ]

09:01.000 --> 09:03.920
Dude, you really need
to get that checked out.

09:03.920 --> 09:06.000
[ Thumping continues
in distance ]

09:06.000 --> 09:09.040
[ Groans ]

09:09.040 --> 09:10.790
Aah!

09:11.880 --> 09:13.960
[ Gasps,
breathing heavily ]

09:13.960 --> 09:16.750
♪♪

09:38.120 --> 09:41.620
No, no. Electronic control units
are sealed against moisture.

09:41.620 --> 09:44.040
Doesn't make it waterproof.
What's our backup plan?

09:44.040 --> 09:45.420
I don't have
a backup plan.

09:45.420 --> 09:47.290
Huck, you have
a backup plan.

09:47.290 --> 09:49.750
♪♪

09:52.080 --> 09:53.960
Air, Huck! Air!

09:57.040 --> 09:59.120
[ Gasps ]

09:59.120 --> 10:01.000
14.7...

10:01.000 --> 10:02.170
25 -- 25...

10:02.170 --> 10:03.040
30 -- 30...

10:03.040 --> 10:04.040
32...

10:04.040 --> 10:05.960
Say, uh, 30 feet.

10:05.960 --> 10:08.830
I could've gone 30 feet
at 32 degrees Fahrenheit,

10:08.830 --> 10:12.710
29.9 inches of mercury
should put PSI at 14.7,

10:12.710 --> 10:14.710
which makes 600 pounds
per square foot.

10:14.710 --> 10:15.920
That's it!

10:15.920 --> 10:17.380
600 pounds.
[ Marker clatters ]

10:17.380 --> 10:18.500
I can open the door.

10:18.500 --> 10:19.670
You can?
Not now.

10:19.670 --> 10:21.170
Not when there's still air
left in the car.

10:21.170 --> 10:23.500
Not when there's 600 pounds
per square foot of pressure

10:23.500 --> 10:24.670
keeping the doors closed.

10:24.670 --> 10:26.120
It wouldn't be
humanly possible

10:26.120 --> 10:28.120
to go up against that
with injuries like mine, but...

10:28.120 --> 10:30.250
If you wait until
the car's inside pressure

10:30.250 --> 10:32.170
is equal to what's
on the outside...

10:32.170 --> 10:34.170
Then we're in business.
You can open the door.

10:34.170 --> 10:35.290
[ Breathes sharply ]

10:35.290 --> 10:36.920
I can open the door.

10:38.830 --> 10:41.040
Huck, what if the doors
don't open?

10:41.040 --> 10:43.670
Liv,
the math is right here.

10:43.670 --> 10:45.420
The doors will open.

10:45.420 --> 10:46.830
-What if you're wrong?
-I'm not wrong.

10:46.830 --> 10:48.460
What if you run out of air

10:48.460 --> 10:49.750
before you can get
the door open?

10:49.750 --> 10:50.920
I won't.

10:50.920 --> 10:52.460
The instant that the car
is fully submerged,

10:52.460 --> 10:53.710
with no air pockets left,

10:53.710 --> 10:55.790
[claps hands]
I make my move.

10:55.790 --> 10:58.580
♪♪

11:05.960 --> 11:08.750
♪♪

11:11.500 --> 11:12.670
It's caught on something.

11:12.670 --> 11:14.250
How can it be caught on
something in the water?

11:14.250 --> 11:15.880
Caught on what?

11:15.880 --> 11:18.920
♪♪

11:23.880 --> 11:25.710
Rocks...and mud.

11:25.710 --> 11:28.210
I-I can't open the door.

11:28.210 --> 11:30.120
[ Glass shattering ]

11:30.120 --> 11:32.420
-No. No, no, no, no, no, no!
-[ Gasps ]

11:32.420 --> 11:35.210
Huck, you have to do
something!
No!

11:39.250 --> 11:40.500
I hate to say,
"I told you so."

11:40.500 --> 11:41.960
Do something!

11:44.250 --> 11:46.080
Rowan: [ Echoing ]
This is not the way I saw
your story ending, son.

11:47.330 --> 11:48.210
It's not the end.

11:48.210 --> 11:50.580
It's the ending!

11:50.580 --> 11:52.880
I trained you. I schooled you.
I taught you.

11:52.880 --> 11:55.250
Was I a fool to believe
that you were listening,

11:55.250 --> 11:56.750
paying attention?

11:56.750 --> 12:01.080
I refuse to believe that
you wasted my time!

12:01.080 --> 12:02.750
I'm sorry.

12:02.750 --> 12:04.040
What?!

12:04.040 --> 12:05.580
I'm -- I'm...

12:05.580 --> 12:08.290
What are you
going to do?!

12:08.290 --> 12:11.790
What can he do?
He's pathetic.

12:11.790 --> 12:13.330
[ Echoing ]
I can't! I can't!

12:13.330 --> 12:15.460
I can't! I can't.

12:15.460 --> 12:17.500
Give it up already.
It's no use.

12:17.500 --> 12:19.000
She's here
to distract you.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.040
I'm here
to finish the job!
[ Gun cocks ]

12:22.250 --> 12:24.120
Dad...
Think, son.

12:24.120 --> 12:27.170
♪♪

12:31.170 --> 12:32.540
[ Groans ]

12:32.540 --> 12:35.420
[ Gasping ]

12:35.420 --> 12:37.830
[ Metal creaks ]

12:37.830 --> 12:40.920
[ Groaning ]

12:40.920 --> 12:42.920
[ Shivering ]

12:42.920 --> 12:45.000
♪♪

12:45.000 --> 12:46.500
Rowan:
Eyes on the prize, soldier.

12:46.500 --> 12:47.750
Meg: He's got 10 seconds
of air left,

12:47.750 --> 12:49.750
11 if he's lucky.

12:49.750 --> 12:51.620
He's not very lucky.

12:51.620 --> 12:53.080
Don't give in.

12:53.080 --> 12:55.670
You have all the tools
you need.

12:55.670 --> 12:57.750
You see it, don't you?
The exact tool.

12:57.750 --> 12:59.210
I just want
to rest my head.

12:59.210 --> 13:01.000
Exactly.
Rest your head.

13:01.000 --> 13:02.750
[ Shivering ]

13:02.750 --> 13:05.540
♪♪

13:17.000 --> 13:18.290
Goodbye, Huck.

13:18.290 --> 13:19.920
[ Gun cocks ]

13:19.920 --> 13:22.960
♪♪

13:25.880 --> 13:27.460
[ Shivering ]

13:27.460 --> 13:30.380
♪♪

13:41.790 --> 13:43.710
[ Glass shatters ]

13:43.710 --> 13:46.500
♪♪

13:49.580 --> 13:51.210
[ Gasping ]

13:55.620 --> 13:57.750
[ Groans, gasping ]

13:57.750 --> 14:00.620
♪♪

14:18.750 --> 14:20.380
[ Breathing quickly ]

14:20.380 --> 14:23.420
♪♪

14:23.420 --> 14:25.960
I can't swim that far.

14:25.960 --> 14:28.000
[ Shuddered breathing ]

14:28.000 --> 14:30.120
I can't do this, Liv.

14:30.120 --> 14:32.880
[ Shuddered breathing ]

14:34.710 --> 14:36.290
Liv?

14:40.330 --> 14:42.040
Liv!

14:43.830 --> 14:45.790
Liv!

14:53.210 --> 14:54.460
What did you do
with Huck?

14:54.460 --> 14:55.920
You're asking
the wrong questions.

14:55.920 --> 14:57.460
I'm gonna give you
five seconds.

14:57.460 --> 14:58.500
If you don't tell me
where Huck is,

14:58.500 --> 14:59.420
I swear, I will --

14:59.420 --> 15:01.420
He's dead.

15:01.420 --> 15:03.120
Look at that --
under five seconds.

15:05.170 --> 15:06.830
You still there?

15:09.750 --> 15:11.540
Why?
Yours is not
to reason why.

15:11.540 --> 15:13.960
Don't you know that?
Yours is just to do or die.

15:13.960 --> 15:15.210
You're an animal.

15:15.210 --> 15:17.620
I am a working girl
with a dream, just like you.

15:17.620 --> 15:19.500
You made a trade,
Ms. Whelan --

15:19.500 --> 15:21.380
Jennifer Fields
for Cyrus Beene.

15:21.380 --> 15:23.710
You did your part,
and if you want us to do ours,

15:23.710 --> 15:26.460
you will shut up and continue
to be collaborative.

15:26.460 --> 15:29.830
You don't want Cyrus to die
in prison, now, do you?

15:29.830 --> 15:31.210
Where's Huck's body?

15:31.210 --> 15:32.960
You know what?
Don't call me again.

15:32.960 --> 15:34.620
I don't like you.

15:34.620 --> 15:36.250
You're annoying.
Please, just tell me
where he is.

15:36.250 --> 15:39.170
That man is my...
[ Cellphone clicks ]

15:39.170 --> 15:40.790
...friend.

15:40.790 --> 15:42.920
[ Door creaks ]

15:42.920 --> 15:44.880
And I thought Meg's place
was supposed to be protected

15:44.880 --> 15:47.000
by one of Huck's souped-up
security systems.

15:53.620 --> 15:55.790
Either she's
been robbed...
Or she's covering
her tracks.

15:55.790 --> 15:58.040
Okay, this girl is part of this,
no question.

15:59.540 --> 16:02.500
She pulled the security-system
control panel.

16:02.500 --> 16:06.000
[ Sighs ] Okay.
What would Huck do?

16:06.000 --> 16:07.670
What about the cloud?
Yeah.

16:07.670 --> 16:08.960
Huck would've backed everything
up with the cloud.

16:08.960 --> 16:10.250
Huck would never
use the cloud.

16:10.250 --> 16:12.120
He doesn't trust the cloud.
The cloud is crap.

16:14.620 --> 16:17.580
If he had backup somewhere,
it would be on...

16:17.580 --> 16:19.500
What?
What would it be on?

16:19.500 --> 16:21.120
[ Breathes sharply ]

16:21.120 --> 16:24.170
♪♪

16:26.380 --> 16:28.080
[ Breathing quickly ]

16:28.080 --> 16:29.120
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

16:29.120 --> 16:31.830
Oh, thank you, Huck.
Thank you, thank you.

16:31.830 --> 16:34.960
What is it?
The cloud can suck it.

16:34.960 --> 16:37.290
Huck likes to back up
on an air-gapped laptop.

16:37.290 --> 16:38.790
[ Sighs ]

16:40.250 --> 16:41.880
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

16:44.790 --> 16:46.000
[ Knock on door ]

16:46.000 --> 16:47.420
Yes?

16:50.420 --> 16:52.080
Abby?

16:52.080 --> 16:54.290
Look,
I'm sorry to bother you,

16:54.290 --> 16:56.620
but it's just --
I mean, you and I get along.

16:56.620 --> 17:00.710
We joke.
We tell each other stuff.

17:00.710 --> 17:02.290
But you're my boss, too, and
that's hard to ignore, I know.

17:02.290 --> 17:04.790
It's hard to separate out.
But...

17:04.790 --> 17:07.040
But just for right now,
for the day,

17:07.040 --> 17:09.830
for 15 minutes,
do you think you could try?

17:09.830 --> 17:11.920
Do you think you could
stop being my boss

17:11.920 --> 17:13.120
and just be my friend?

17:13.120 --> 17:15.210
Because I really need
a friend right now.

17:15.210 --> 17:18.830
I need to talk to a friend,
and you are...

17:18.830 --> 17:21.920
These days, you...

17:21.920 --> 17:23.790
You're the only
real friend I have.

17:26.120 --> 17:27.540
Close the door.

17:27.540 --> 17:30.580
♪♪

17:32.330 --> 17:34.000
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

17:38.710 --> 17:40.120
[ Footsteps approaching ]

17:40.120 --> 17:41.880
[ Door closes ]

17:44.170 --> 17:46.210
What can I do?

17:49.880 --> 17:52.250
What are you doing here?

17:52.250 --> 17:55.420
Huck's missing.

17:55.420 --> 17:56.750
How can I help?

17:56.750 --> 17:58.830
We're working on it.

17:58.830 --> 17:59.960
There's nothing
for you to do.

17:59.960 --> 18:01.080
Go back to work.
I'll keep you posted.

18:01.080 --> 18:02.830
Yeah, you will --

18:02.830 --> 18:04.500
because I'll be sitting
at the conference table

18:04.500 --> 18:07.170
until you hear something
or you need me.

18:08.920 --> 18:10.670
Marcus...

18:15.000 --> 18:17.500
Can you
just sit here with me?

18:30.250 --> 18:31.880
[ Sighs ]

18:31.880 --> 18:33.920
[ Gasping ]

18:39.170 --> 18:40.920
[ Groaning ]

18:42.670 --> 18:44.080
[ Wind rushing ]

18:44.080 --> 18:45.880
[ Groaning ]

18:53.170 --> 18:54.880
[ Panting ]

18:58.580 --> 18:59.920
Huck:
You've gone soft.

19:03.960 --> 19:05.920
[ Breathing heavily ]

19:09.170 --> 19:12.250
Y-You don't know.

19:12.250 --> 19:14.500
You want to die?

19:14.500 --> 19:16.380
I don't have anything
to slice and dice with,

19:16.380 --> 19:19.210
but I could just watch
until your organs shut down

19:19.210 --> 19:21.670
from lack of oxygen
due to blood loss.

19:21.670 --> 19:23.380
That might be fun.

19:26.500 --> 19:27.500
[ Groans ]

19:27.500 --> 19:29.790
Don't start believing
in yourself.

19:29.790 --> 19:31.580
[ Panting ]
Just shut up.

19:31.580 --> 19:35.460
Hey, you know
what time it is?

19:35.460 --> 19:37.330
Look at your watch.

19:37.330 --> 19:39.120
Go on, look.

19:42.040 --> 19:44.750
It's 7:52.

19:44.750 --> 19:47.330
7:52.

19:47.330 --> 19:48.420
[ Echoing ]
7:52...7:52...

19:48.420 --> 19:50.540
7:52, 7:52.

19:50.540 --> 19:51.750
Shut up.

19:51.750 --> 19:55.000
Come dark,
you're coyote chum, bro.

19:55.000 --> 19:57.460
You were better off
in the trunk.

19:57.460 --> 19:58.670
[ Whispering ]
They're gonna find me.

19:58.670 --> 19:59.880
What was that?

19:59.880 --> 20:01.380
[ Louder ]
They're gonna find me.

20:01.380 --> 20:02.670
[ Laughs ]

20:02.670 --> 20:04.540
No one's looking for you.

20:04.540 --> 20:07.080
Go away.
Not a single person.

20:07.080 --> 20:08.790
Just go away!

20:08.790 --> 20:10.080
[ Breathes sharply ]

20:10.080 --> 20:11.580
I said, "Go away"!

20:11.580 --> 20:14.580
♪♪

20:26.000 --> 20:28.040
Am I a good boss?

20:28.040 --> 20:29.880
You want to blame
yourself for this?

20:29.880 --> 20:31.250
Am I a good boss?

20:31.250 --> 20:32.380
Olivia, three years ago,

20:32.380 --> 20:35.790
I was at whatever
below rock bottom is.

20:35.790 --> 20:36.830
I am where I am
because of you,

20:36.830 --> 20:39.120
because
you always had my back.

20:40.880 --> 20:44.040
Huck knows that, too.

20:44.040 --> 20:46.210
He knows
you got his back.

20:49.210 --> 20:51.040
Hey. No luck identifying
your mystery duo yet,

20:51.040 --> 20:52.580
but I did get a hit
on that Meg girl.

20:52.580 --> 20:55.620
♪♪

20:57.330 --> 20:58.830
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

20:58.830 --> 21:00.670
[ Elevator bell dings ]

21:05.080 --> 21:06.830
Liv, there's something
that we need to --

21:06.830 --> 21:08.120
Oh!

21:08.120 --> 21:09.250
What did I tell you?

21:09.250 --> 21:10.380
I -- I --

21:10.380 --> 21:13.330
[ Groans ]
What did I tell you?!

21:13.330 --> 21:14.460
Jake: Liv?
[ Breathes sharply ]

21:14.460 --> 21:17.500
♪♪

21:20.170 --> 21:23.080
What did I tell you?

21:23.080 --> 21:26.250
Liv, I --
Do not cross me again!

21:26.250 --> 21:27.880
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

21:27.880 --> 21:29.080
I'm sorry, Liv.
I'm so, so --

21:29.080 --> 21:30.420
Where is he?
I don't know.

21:30.420 --> 21:32.580
Where is Huck?
I don't know!

21:32.580 --> 21:35.460
Aah!

21:35.460 --> 21:36.500
Tell me everything.

21:36.500 --> 21:38.420
Ohh. Liv, please!

21:38.420 --> 21:39.920
Everything!

21:39.920 --> 21:43.080
♪♪

21:43.080 --> 21:45.620
[ Faucet running ]

21:45.620 --> 21:47.620
[ Faucet shuts off ]

21:50.290 --> 21:52.750
[ Sighs ]

21:52.750 --> 21:54.830
[ Floorboards creak ]

21:54.830 --> 21:56.750
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

22:00.830 --> 22:02.460
[ Floorboards creak ]

22:02.460 --> 22:05.500
[ Music continues ]

22:15.750 --> 22:17.330
[ Floorboards creak ]

22:17.330 --> 22:19.120
[ Music continues ]

22:39.540 --> 22:41.620
[ Silenced gunshots ]

22:46.170 --> 22:48.120
[ Rats squeaking ]
[ Gasps ]

22:48.120 --> 22:49.460
[ Music stops ]

22:58.420 --> 23:02.460
[ Music resumes ]
Where is he?

23:02.460 --> 23:04.580
[ Breathing heavily ]

23:04.580 --> 23:07.620
♪♪

23:08.210 --> 23:10.250
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

23:10.250 --> 23:12.580
Jennifer for Cyrus --
that was the deal I made --

23:12.580 --> 23:15.000
that's it, I swear.

23:15.000 --> 23:17.120
So, help me understand.

23:17.120 --> 23:19.580
You kill Huck,
frame Cyrus.

23:19.580 --> 23:21.750
For what?
What did they give you?

23:21.750 --> 23:24.960
What was your best outcome
for selling out your family?

23:24.960 --> 23:27.380
I had no idea
they would harm Huck.

23:27.380 --> 23:28.540
And you have
just as much blame

23:28.540 --> 23:30.500
for Cyrus rotting in jail
as I do.

23:30.500 --> 23:33.120
I have done everything
in my power to get him out

23:33.120 --> 23:34.960
while you have done everything
in your power to keep him in,

23:34.960 --> 23:36.580
to turn a blind eye
to his innocence

23:36.580 --> 23:37.960
to protect your father,

23:37.960 --> 23:39.330
to protect
your place in the Oval.

23:39.330 --> 23:41.420
You knew Cyrus was innocent,
but you still --

23:41.420 --> 23:44.210
Huck might be dead.

23:44.210 --> 23:46.670
My Huck.

23:46.670 --> 23:47.710
You really want
to lecture me right now?

23:47.710 --> 23:48.880
You think I'm in the mood?

23:48.880 --> 23:50.080
Do you think
I won't get a chair

23:50.080 --> 23:52.120
and work it out
on you?

23:52.120 --> 23:53.960
♪♪

23:53.960 --> 23:56.580
I'm not making excuses.

23:56.580 --> 23:58.290
I'm just asking --

23:58.290 --> 24:00.460
begging you
to forgive me,

24:00.460 --> 24:01.920
just as I have
forgiven you.

24:01.920 --> 24:03.620
We all have
over and over.

24:03.620 --> 24:07.040
Don't tell me you're
the only one who gets forgiven.

24:07.040 --> 24:09.830
All I ask is that you see that
and that you try, please try.

24:09.830 --> 24:11.790
I'm asking you
one more time.

24:11.790 --> 24:14.210
Can you help find Huck?

24:17.540 --> 24:20.460
Yes or no?

24:20.460 --> 24:21.920
No.

24:21.920 --> 24:24.620
♪♪

24:26.790 --> 24:28.750
Then you're worthless.

24:30.330 --> 24:31.710
[ Footsteps ]

24:31.710 --> 24:34.790
♪♪

24:34.790 --> 24:36.500
Where do you think
you're going?

24:39.790 --> 24:41.210
You think
I'm gonna let you out

24:41.210 --> 24:45.210
so you can go get protection
from your friends?

24:45.210 --> 24:46.830
Get in there.

24:46.830 --> 24:48.170
You get in there

24:48.170 --> 24:49.670
and wait till Quinn
finds out what you did

24:49.670 --> 24:51.960
and, Abby,
I will not call her off.

24:51.960 --> 24:53.960
I will not save you
from her.

24:53.960 --> 24:57.460
I will applaud whatever way
she chooses to express her rage.

24:57.460 --> 25:00.120
So you better pray to God

25:00.120 --> 25:02.120
that when we find Huck,
he's alive.

25:02.120 --> 25:03.790
That's your only chance

25:03.790 --> 25:06.670
because whatever cliff
Quinn wants to go over,

25:06.670 --> 25:08.290
I'm going over with her.

25:10.670 --> 25:13.250
You messed
with the wrong gladiator.

25:13.250 --> 25:14.500
[ Door opens ]

25:14.500 --> 25:17.500
♪♪

25:28.420 --> 25:31.620
♪♪

25:31.620 --> 25:34.000
[ Panting ]

25:34.000 --> 25:35.960
[ Insects chirping ]

25:40.170 --> 25:42.170
[ Groaning ]

25:42.170 --> 25:45.210
♪♪

25:49.250 --> 25:50.960
[ Thuds ]

25:50.960 --> 25:53.000
[ Breathing heavily ]

25:53.000 --> 25:55.790
♪♪

26:09.920 --> 26:11.880
[ Muffled groaning ]

26:14.000 --> 26:15.750
[ Screaming ]

26:19.290 --> 26:20.620
You want to tell us
where Huck is?

26:20.620 --> 26:22.080
Mnh!

26:22.080 --> 26:23.380
No, no, no, no.
You look at me.

26:23.380 --> 26:26.830
Look...at...me.

26:26.830 --> 26:28.830
Where is Huck?

26:28.830 --> 26:31.040
[ Grunting ]

26:31.040 --> 26:33.830
♪♪

26:37.040 --> 26:39.960
[ Grunts ]
[ Screaming ]

26:39.960 --> 26:43.210
Was it this finger
that pulled the trigger

26:43.210 --> 26:45.460
when you shot my friend?

26:45.460 --> 26:46.880
Can't be sure?

26:46.880 --> 26:48.290
Okay.

26:50.080 --> 26:51.540
[ Muffled screaming ]

26:54.540 --> 26:57.040
Everyone talks eventually.
You're going to talk.

26:57.040 --> 26:58.880
I just haven't hit
the right nerve.

27:01.460 --> 27:02.710
You know, some people,
you can do

27:02.710 --> 27:03.880
whatever you want to them
below their neck

27:03.880 --> 27:06.330
because it's their face
they want to protect.

27:06.330 --> 27:09.580
It's the first thing
people protect in a fight.

27:09.580 --> 27:11.170
You can train someone
to deal with pain,

27:11.170 --> 27:13.500
but vanity [chuckles] --

27:13.500 --> 27:16.710
that's something
way deeper.

27:16.710 --> 27:18.620
You want to tell me
where Huck is?

27:18.620 --> 27:20.960
[ Whimpering ]

27:20.960 --> 27:24.290
[ Groaning ]

27:24.290 --> 27:26.380
[ Grunts ]

27:26.380 --> 27:27.210
[ Instrument slicing ]

27:27.210 --> 27:28.540
[ Panting ]

27:28.540 --> 27:32.620
Now...I'm gonna take
this tape off,

27:32.620 --> 27:34.330
and you're gonna
tell me about Huck.

27:34.330 --> 27:36.790
[ Crying ]
Huh?

27:36.790 --> 27:38.380
Huh?

27:38.380 --> 27:40.960
♪♪

27:44.380 --> 27:47.830
No wonder Huck loved me
instead of you.

27:47.830 --> 27:48.880
[ Spits ]

27:48.880 --> 27:50.460
You tell me where he is!
No! No, no, no,
no, no, no!

27:50.460 --> 27:52.080
You talk! You talk!
You talk!

27:52.080 --> 27:53.880
[ Gasps ]

27:53.880 --> 27:55.380
-[ Grunts ]
-No!

27:57.330 --> 27:58.620
Easy.

27:58.620 --> 28:01.080
[ Crying ]

28:01.080 --> 28:02.830
She's dead.

28:03.960 --> 28:05.880
[ Panting ]

28:05.880 --> 28:08.500
♪♪

28:12.000 --> 28:13.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

28:13.460 --> 28:14.710
Jake: Damn!
Olivia: What?

28:14.710 --> 28:16.000
Well, I finally broke
through the vertical code

28:16.000 --> 28:17.710
and rotary-frame software
that Huck uses

28:17.710 --> 28:20.460
to scramble the location signal
emitting from his phone.

28:20.460 --> 28:23.040
Good.
That's good, right?

28:23.040 --> 28:26.710
Well, I was hoping it would be,
but the last ping on Huck

28:26.710 --> 28:28.120
put him in the motel
where Jennifer was.

28:28.120 --> 28:29.380
Seven hours since,
no signal.

28:29.380 --> 28:31.250
That just means
his phone is off or lost.

28:31.250 --> 28:32.460
It's not
necessarily bad news.

28:32.460 --> 28:34.210
Bad news.

28:34.210 --> 28:35.750
You couldn't find Meg?

28:35.750 --> 28:38.460
We found her, but I promise
she ain't talking.

28:42.290 --> 28:44.960
Hmm.
What did you do?

28:49.170 --> 28:51.040
Did it feel good?

28:51.040 --> 28:53.330
I hope so.

28:53.330 --> 28:54.830
Because now we have
no leads --

28:54.830 --> 28:56.620
zero, none.

28:56.620 --> 28:59.540
Meg was our last hope
at finding Huck alive.

28:59.540 --> 29:02.080
♪♪

29:02.080 --> 29:04.540
[ Footsteps ]

29:04.540 --> 29:05.540
Liv.

29:05.540 --> 29:08.210
[ Door opens, slams shut ]

29:08.210 --> 29:11.250
♪♪

29:14.960 --> 29:17.330
Okay.
What next?

29:18.120 --> 29:20.710
He's dead.

29:20.710 --> 29:23.000
We've been doing this
a long time.

29:23.000 --> 29:24.750
Huck is dead.

29:24.750 --> 29:27.540
♪♪

29:38.330 --> 29:39.750
[ Door opens ]

29:39.750 --> 29:41.880
Get out.

29:41.880 --> 29:43.420
Yeah, I can't do that.

29:43.420 --> 29:45.040
Charlie, if you know
what's good for you --

29:45.040 --> 29:46.830
I don't ever know
what's good for me.

29:46.830 --> 29:47.880
That's not really
how I roll.

29:47.880 --> 29:49.290
Now is not the time.

29:49.290 --> 29:50.960
You have to do something.

29:52.620 --> 29:54.830
For them, all of them.
They need you right now.

29:54.830 --> 29:56.500
Quinn -- Quinn, especially,
needs you right now,

29:56.500 --> 29:57.960
so you have
to do something.

29:57.960 --> 29:59.170
What do you
want me to do?

30:01.380 --> 30:03.920
What, Charlie? What exactly
do you think I'm supposed to do?

30:03.920 --> 30:07.170
Fix this.
Fix them.

30:07.170 --> 30:09.210
You know, the whole
"Olivia Pope" thing that you do,

30:09.210 --> 30:11.500
the speech-y thing where you
get up in their grills

30:11.500 --> 30:12.960
and get all serious
and mean.

30:12.960 --> 30:14.330
Mean?

30:14.330 --> 30:16.790
Well, I -- yeah,
I think you're kind of mean.

30:16.790 --> 30:18.420
Sometimes you're not
really very nice to me.

30:18.420 --> 30:20.540
[ Breathes sharply ]
I said sometimes.

30:20.540 --> 30:21.750
You know, with the stomping
around and the --

30:21.750 --> 30:23.830
what are those --
opera gloves, right?

30:23.830 --> 30:25.830
You know, those are a bit much,
but they work for the thing,

30:25.830 --> 30:28.540
your thing, the white-hat
gladiator thing that you do.

30:31.420 --> 30:34.000
Fix them.

30:34.000 --> 30:36.380
Huck is dead, Charlie.

30:39.540 --> 30:41.380
I can't fix anybody.

30:42.670 --> 30:44.330
[ Breathes sharply ]

30:48.750 --> 30:51.000
Quinn's gonna
want to see a body.

30:51.000 --> 30:53.620
You get that, right?

30:53.620 --> 30:55.710
She's not gonna be okay
until she sees a body,

30:55.710 --> 30:57.670
a bloated, rotting,
full-of-pus, bona fide body,

30:57.670 --> 31:00.170
so you still have
to find him, Olivia.

31:00.170 --> 31:01.960
He would want to be found.

31:01.960 --> 31:03.540
You can't just give up.

31:03.540 --> 31:05.670
You don't just give up --
that's not part of the thing.

31:05.670 --> 31:08.170
The thing requires you to,
above all things,

31:08.170 --> 31:09.250
perform miracles,

31:09.250 --> 31:12.750
and you are
a miracle worker.

31:12.750 --> 31:13.880
Look what happened
with me.

31:13.880 --> 31:16.880
I -- I'm gonna be
somebody's husband.

31:16.880 --> 31:18.420
I might be a dad.

31:18.420 --> 31:19.380
You've got me here
doing good deeds,

31:19.380 --> 31:21.290
which means hell
has frozen over.

31:21.290 --> 31:22.580
You pulled off
the impossible.

31:22.580 --> 31:25.380
You made hell freeze over --
miracle.

31:25.380 --> 31:27.580
You can't quit.
You don't quit.

31:27.580 --> 31:31.000
Miracle workers
don't get to quit.

31:31.000 --> 31:35.790
♪ Good morn or evening,
friends ♪

31:35.790 --> 31:37.330
♪ Here's your
friendly announcer ♪

31:37.330 --> 31:40.500
The thing also requires
you to speak.

31:40.500 --> 31:43.330
♪ I have serious news ♪

31:43.330 --> 31:48.710
♪ To pass on to everybody ♪

31:48.710 --> 31:50.290
Everyone,
conference room, now!

31:50.290 --> 31:55.170
♪ What I'm about to say ♪

31:55.170 --> 31:57.880
We're not giving up.
♪ Could mean
the world's disaster ♪

31:57.880 --> 31:59.380
This is Huck, our Huck.

31:59.380 --> 32:01.290
He belongs to us.
♪ Could change your joy
and laughter to tears and pain ♪

32:01.290 --> 32:03.620
He deserves
to come home to us,

32:03.620 --> 32:06.080
and that means
whether he's alive or dead.

32:06.080 --> 32:08.710
I don't care what it takes.
I don't care how long it takes.

32:08.710 --> 32:10.460
Hell could freeze over,
and guess what.

32:10.460 --> 32:12.170
You wouldn't care.
I would not care.

32:12.170 --> 32:16.250
♪ It's that love's
in need of love today ♪

32:16.250 --> 32:18.620
We're pulling off
the impossible.

32:18.620 --> 32:20.500
We're doing what we do.
♪ Don't delay ♪

32:20.500 --> 32:22.290
And if what's required,

32:22.290 --> 32:24.040
if what needs to take place
is a miracle...

32:24.040 --> 32:25.380
♪ Send yours in right away ♪
...then so be it.

32:25.380 --> 32:28.580
We make that miracle happen.

32:28.580 --> 32:33.290
♪ Hate's goin' 'round ♪

32:33.290 --> 32:36.460
♪ Breaking many hearts ♪
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

32:38.170 --> 32:42.620
♪ Stop it, please ♪

32:42.620 --> 32:46.380
♪ Before it's gone too far ♪

32:46.380 --> 32:48.330
This isn't a request...

32:48.330 --> 32:52.290
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

32:52.290 --> 32:53.790
♪ Oh, whoa ♪

32:53.790 --> 32:55.750
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

32:55.750 --> 32:59.790
♪ Oh, whoa ♪

32:59.790 --> 33:00.830
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

33:00.830 --> 33:05.210
♪ The force of evil plans ♪

33:05.210 --> 33:06.290
♪ To make you its possession ♪

33:06.290 --> 33:10.290
-Where are you, Huck?
-[ Sighs ]

33:10.290 --> 33:12.290
♪ And it will, if we let it,
destroy everybody ♪
It's not just Huck.

33:12.290 --> 33:13.670
What?
[ Sighs ]

33:13.670 --> 33:15.420
It's not just Huck.

33:15.420 --> 33:17.000
He's not the only one
out there.
Jennifer.

33:17.000 --> 33:18.670
She's with him, too.
Wherever she is...

33:18.670 --> 33:19.670
Huck is.

33:19.670 --> 33:21.710
So we focus
on finding Jennifer.

33:21.710 --> 33:23.750
♪ We all must take... ♪
She has a phone.
I gave her one just in case.

33:23.750 --> 33:25.330
You can track it down,
triangulate her signal.

33:25.330 --> 33:27.210
We can find Huck.
We can bring him home.

33:27.210 --> 33:30.000
♪ ...precautionary measures ♪

33:30.000 --> 33:33.670
♪ If love and peace
you treasure ♪

33:33.670 --> 33:37.790
♪ Then you'll hear me
when I say ♪

33:37.790 --> 33:39.540
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, that love's
in need of love today ♪

33:39.540 --> 33:40.960
Her cell stopped
sending signal hours ago

33:40.960 --> 33:41.920
which mean could mean
she turned it off,

33:41.920 --> 33:43.500
but it could also mean
it's damaged.

33:43.500 --> 33:47.000
Last recorded signal was,
uh, about 50 yards this way.

33:47.000 --> 33:50.000
[ Sighs ] Anything?
♪ Don't delay ♪

33:50.000 --> 33:51.920
We should have
gone with them.

33:51.920 --> 33:54.120
You know, I --
I have to do something.
♪ Send yours in right away ♪

33:54.120 --> 33:56.750
Robin.
We're supposed to be
keeping an eye on Abby.

33:56.750 --> 33:57.830
What do you mean?
♪ Hate's goin' 'round ♪

33:57.830 --> 33:59.620
That's what Liv told me
before she left.

33:59.620 --> 34:01.290
That's weird.

34:01.290 --> 34:03.330
Why in the hell would we have
to keep an eye on you?

34:03.330 --> 34:08.120
♪ Breaking hearts ♪
♪ Breaking many hearts ♪

34:08.120 --> 34:11.750
♪ Stop it, please ♪
I'm sorry.

34:11.750 --> 34:13.920
♪ Before it's gone too far ♪
What did you do?

34:13.920 --> 34:15.290
I -- Quinn, I'm --

34:15.290 --> 34:16.580
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Quinn!

34:16.580 --> 34:18.290
It was you?!
♪ It's up to you ♪

34:18.290 --> 34:19.540
Okay, calm down!
Come on.

34:19.540 --> 34:22.460
I will kill you!

34:22.460 --> 34:25.080
♪ 'Cause love's in need
of love today ♪

34:25.080 --> 34:27.790
♪ Today ♪

34:27.790 --> 34:29.670
♪ Don't delay ♪
There. There!

34:29.670 --> 34:31.210
[ Panting ]

34:31.210 --> 34:35.960
♪ Send yours in right away ♪
[ Both panting ]

34:35.960 --> 34:37.380
♪ You know
that hate's goin' 'round ♪

34:37.380 --> 34:39.420
Jake, is he...?
Huck, can you
say something, buddy?

34:39.420 --> 34:41.620
It's okay.
I'm -- I'm here.
Huck?

34:41.620 --> 34:44.080
♪ Bring it down a little ♪
I'm here now.
It's okay, Huck. Huck.

34:44.080 --> 34:45.960
♪ Love is very peaceful ♪
It's okay.

34:45.960 --> 34:47.880
♪ So bring it down a little ♪
It's all right.
I'm here now.

34:47.880 --> 34:48.620
♪ Yes ♪
It's okay.

34:53.670 --> 34:55.750
[ Sighs ]

34:55.750 --> 34:58.380
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

34:58.380 --> 35:00.330
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

35:07.830 --> 35:09.290
Is he okay?

35:09.290 --> 35:11.460
He's stable for now
and breathing on his own.

35:11.460 --> 35:13.670
We were able to remove the
bullets and stop the bleeding.

35:13.670 --> 35:16.080
But is he okay?

35:16.080 --> 35:17.960
Your friend lost
a lot of blood tonight,

35:17.960 --> 35:20.380
putting him at risk
of permanent brain damage.

35:20.380 --> 35:21.540
You should be prepared

35:21.540 --> 35:23.540
for him to wake up
with severe deficits

35:23.540 --> 35:24.920
or not wake up at all.

35:27.210 --> 35:30.170
Right now,
rest is the best thing for him.

35:30.170 --> 35:32.330
And for all of you.

35:32.330 --> 35:35.250
You should go home,
try to get some sleep.

35:45.120 --> 35:47.580
♪♪

35:47.580 --> 35:49.000
Liv.

35:51.380 --> 35:53.460
Oh, crap.

35:53.460 --> 35:56.250
♪♪

36:09.250 --> 36:11.210
[ Sniffles ]

36:11.210 --> 36:13.330
[ Sighs ]

36:13.330 --> 36:14.380
How's he doing?

36:14.380 --> 36:16.500
[ Sighs ]

36:21.080 --> 36:23.000
Liv.

36:26.710 --> 36:29.500
[ Sniffles ]

36:29.500 --> 36:31.790
He might die.

36:34.040 --> 36:36.750
Come here.

36:36.750 --> 36:38.540
I'm so sorry.

36:38.540 --> 36:41.580
♪♪

36:41.580 --> 36:43.830
[ Crying, sniffling ]

36:43.830 --> 36:46.880
♪♪

36:54.830 --> 36:56.580
[ Sighs, sniffles ]

36:56.580 --> 36:57.710
How's your team?

36:57.710 --> 36:59.830
Oh...

36:59.830 --> 37:02.040
Do they need anything?

37:02.040 --> 37:05.380
They'll --
They'll rely on each other.

37:05.380 --> 37:08.120
If he dies, they'll...

37:08.120 --> 37:09.880
get through it together.

37:12.080 --> 37:13.460
And Abby?

37:15.670 --> 37:16.670
What about Abby?

37:16.670 --> 37:18.330
She told me.

37:19.460 --> 37:20.620
Everything.

37:22.540 --> 37:24.540
That was selfish.

37:24.540 --> 37:28.880
You don't force the president
to keep that kind of secret.

37:28.880 --> 37:30.960
That's making you
commit treason.

37:30.960 --> 37:33.210
You need
to forgive her.

37:33.210 --> 37:35.620
I know you don't want
to hear that, but, Liv...

37:35.620 --> 37:37.460
Someone put three bullets
in Huck

37:37.460 --> 37:39.080
and left him for dead

37:39.080 --> 37:42.500
in the bottom
of a quarry.

37:42.500 --> 37:44.750
He's being kept alive
by machines.

37:44.750 --> 37:46.040
[ Sighs ]

37:48.210 --> 37:51.540
You're telling me
I need to forgive her?

37:51.540 --> 37:55.880
Abby, the person who put him
in that hospital bed?

37:55.880 --> 37:58.000
I do not
have to forgive her.

37:58.000 --> 37:59.710
You forgave me.

38:01.880 --> 38:03.080
That was different.

38:03.080 --> 38:04.830
I forgave you.

38:07.670 --> 38:10.920
You know what happens to you
when you're in that Oval.

38:10.920 --> 38:13.880
You know what lengths
you can find yourself going to

38:13.880 --> 38:16.830
in order to stay there.

38:16.830 --> 38:18.880
But you also know
how to get out.

38:21.330 --> 38:25.000
She needs you.

38:25.000 --> 38:27.880
If anyone can pull her back,
if anyone can save her,

38:27.880 --> 38:31.250
it's the one person
who got out.

38:31.250 --> 38:33.040
It's Olivia Pope.

38:33.040 --> 38:36.290
♪♪

38:36.290 --> 38:38.330
[ Monitor beeping ]

38:43.580 --> 38:46.120
God, how could you
be so stupid?

38:46.120 --> 38:48.830
How can you look out
for everyone around you

38:48.830 --> 38:51.210
and not see danger looking you
right in the face?

38:51.210 --> 38:53.790
I mean, what the hell
is wrong with you?

38:53.790 --> 38:55.000
How many times
does this have to happen?

38:55.000 --> 38:56.290
When are you
going to realize

38:56.290 --> 38:58.420
that the only people
who really love you

38:58.420 --> 39:01.620
are right next to you,
huh?

39:01.620 --> 39:04.920
God, answer that,
you idiot.

39:04.920 --> 39:06.290
[ Sniffles ]

39:08.170 --> 39:11.210
Okay.
[ Sighs ]

39:11.210 --> 39:14.210
Okay.

39:14.210 --> 39:16.080
You have a blind spot.

39:16.080 --> 39:17.500
Fine.

39:17.500 --> 39:19.040
But you're an idiot.

39:19.040 --> 39:21.330
Fine.

39:21.330 --> 39:24.330
From now on,
I'll look out for you.

39:24.330 --> 39:27.290
I'll cover your blind spot,
I promise.

39:27.290 --> 39:30.420
You just need to...

39:30.420 --> 39:33.040
not die.

39:33.040 --> 39:35.000
I'll never forgive you
if you die.

39:35.000 --> 39:36.670
[ Beeping continues ]

39:47.460 --> 39:48.670
[ "God Bless the Child" plays ]

39:48.670 --> 39:50.960
I'm so sorry, Huck.
[ Crying ]

39:50.960 --> 39:52.920
[ Music continues ]

39:58.330 --> 39:59.920
[ Gasps ]

39:59.920 --> 40:01.750
[ Music continues ]

40:03.790 --> 40:10.290
♪ Them that's got shall get ♪

40:10.290 --> 40:15.210
♪ Them that's not shall lose ♪

40:15.210 --> 40:19.170
♪ For the Bible said

40:19.170 --> 40:23.710
♪ And it still is news ♪

40:23.710 --> 40:27.750
♪ Mama may have ♪

40:27.750 --> 40:31.250
♪ Papa may have ♪
[ Sniffles ]

40:31.250 --> 40:33.540
♪ God bless the child ♪

40:33.540 --> 40:39.000
[ Sniffles ]
♪ That's got his own ♪

40:39.000 --> 40:42.540
♪ That's got his own ♪

40:45.170 --> 40:51.540
♪ While the strong gets more ♪

40:51.540 --> 40:55.960
♪ While the weak ones fade ♪

40:55.960 --> 41:01.880
♪ Empty pockets don't
ever make the grade ♪

41:01.880 --> 41:04.540
♪ No, no ♪

41:04.540 --> 41:08.920
♪ Mama may have ♪

41:08.920 --> 41:12.250
♪ Papa may have ♪

41:12.250 --> 41:17.500
♪ But God bless the child
that can stand up anywhere ♪

41:17.500 --> 41:22.330
♪ And say, "I've got my own" ♪

41:22.330 --> 41:26.170
♪ Whoa, oh ♪

41:26.170 --> 41:30.460
♪ Now, rich relations
will give you ♪

41:30.460 --> 41:34.620
♪ A crust of bread and such ♪

41:34.620 --> 41:37.790
♪ Now, you can help yourself ♪

41:37.790 --> 41:41.170
♪ Oh, but don't take --
don't take too much ♪

41:41.170 --> 41:44.250
♪ No, no ♪

41:44.250 --> 41:46.920
♪ Mama may have ♪
[ Crying ]

41:46.920 --> 41:51.120
♪ Mm, and Papa may have ♪

41:51.120 --> 41:55.380
♪ But God bless the child ♪

41:55.380 --> 41:57.580
♪ It's always a child ♪

41:57.580 --> 42:04.000
♪ That can say,
"I've got my own" ♪

42:04.000 --> 42:05.380
[ Crying ]

42:05.380 --> 42:08.420
♪ Whoa-oh ♪

42:08.420 --> 42:14.000
♪ I've got my own ♪
[ Sobbing ]

42:14.000 --> 42:15.170
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

42:22.000 --> 42:25.040
♪♪
